Brazilian Stock Movers: CSN, Minas Gerais,Natura, Tele Norte

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-03-29T21:45:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/brazilian-stock-movers-gafisa-csn-tele-norte-minas-gerais.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.3 percent to 67,418.76.  Natura Cosmeticos SA (NATU3 BS), Latin America’s largest
cosmetics maker, surged 3 percent to 45.70 after the central
bank said total credit, an indication of domestic demand,
expanded 1.3 percent in February.  Tele Norte Leste Participacoes SA (TNLP3)  (TNLP3 BS), Brazil’s
biggest fixed-line phone company, rose 2.5 percent to 38.70
reais as Portugal Telecom SGPS SA bought 25.3 percent of Telemar
Norte Leste for 8.32 billion reais. Telemar Norte Leste, known
as Oi, is a unit of Tele Norte Leste. Portugal Telecom aims to
tap growing demand for mobile-phone and Internet services in
Brazil.  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA (USIM5)  (USIM3 BS), Brazil’s
second-biggest steelmaker, rose 1.4 percent to 29.20 reais, as
CSN Chief Financial Officer Paulo Penido said his company is
aiming for a 10 percent stake in its rival. CSN increased its
stake in Usiminas to 8.62 percent as of March 21.  Cia. Siderurgica Naciona SA (CSNA3 BS),  Brazil ’s third-
largest steelmaker, advanced 1.1 percent to 26.85 reais, its
highest price in five weeks, as CSN’s Penido said his company
aims to retain its 19.9 percent stake in Riversdale Mining Ltd.
Rio Tinto Group is seeking to buy a controlling stake in Sydney-
based Riversdale, two people with knowledge of the matter told
Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
